Hi Gorka, did you try following the instructions provided in the error message? In order to build optional components you need to set an environment variable before building. Try:

{code:R}
Sys.setenv(LIBARROW_MINIMAL = "false")
install.packages("arrow")
{code}

Hi Will. Thanks! Setting the environment variable solved the problem. 

I didn't realize that the hint was from the R package, I thought it was from the cpp library itself. Perhaps, it would be clearer with an R error message like:

{code:r}
 * Sys.setenv(LIBARROW_MINIMAL="false") (for all optional features, including 'snappy')
 * Sys.setenv(ARROW_WITH_SNAPPY="ON") (for just 'snappy')
{code}
